{
  "stem": "4830.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They did not really worry too much about names.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this is how we lived in those days in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There was a constant fear of deporting Budapest.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And just to characterize our frame of mind, one time there was a news coming to us to Szob that they are going to deport the population of Budapest.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And my main concern was my younger brother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I know I told that I cannot do very much for my parents and for my sister, so I smuggled him out of Budapest and smuggled him into our units, which I considered safe.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It wasn't, but I considered it safe.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he was there for a few days until this rumor died down.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then I smuggled him back to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "This summer was a very long and hot summer in every way, and we managed to leave.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The whole family was-- my older brother, and me with the military units, and the rest of my family in their own apartments-- in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in several of my escapes, there was one last one, which already occurred from Csepel, because we were transferred back to Csepel from Szob.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Finally they hit the bridge, and it was completely destroyed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We had no real fixing it, so they returned us to this factory.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And at one of my escape, they discovered us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they came to us-- they knew that--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were the--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "These were members of the Hungarian army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Every labor unit like this was composed of about 160 to 200 members of the unit, and then to guard us and to lead us.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were 14, 15 soldiers who were-- they called it the frame.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were framing the unit.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
